Could you try the following patch and send a pull request to Homebrew if this works?

{noformat}
diff --git a/Formula/apache-arrow.rb b/Formula/apache-arrow.rb
index 3c11899d12e..d5c46061831 100644
--- a/Formula/apache-arrow.rb
+++ b/Formula/apache-arrow.rb
@@ -58,7 +58,7 @@ class ApacheArrow < Formula
       -DARROW_WITH_BROTLI=ON
       -DARROW_WITH_UTF8PROC=ON
       -DARROW_INSTALL_NAME_RPATH=OFF
-      -DPYTHON_EXECUTABLE=#{Formula["python@3.9"].bin/"python3"}
+      -DPython3_EXECUTABLE=#{Formula["python@3.9"].bin/"python3"}
     ]
 
     args << "-DARROW_MIMALLOC=ON" unless Hardware::CPU.arm?
{noformat}

Both Python and NumPy are installed as part of the arrow installation with homebrew {{brew install apache-arrow --HEAD}}. There is no error message when installing either of them. The error message surfaces a bit later with:
{code}
Could NOT find Python3 (missing: Python3_NumPy_INCLUDE_DIRS NumPy) (found
 version "3.9.7")
{code}
